        <p>A relationship table is an element used to link related topics together. It is similar to concept links or related topics links<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.FlareOnlineOnly"><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.FlareOnlineOnly"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../Concepts/Inserting_Concept_Links.htm">Inserting Concept Links into Topics</MadCap:xref> and <MadCap:xref href="../../../Nav_Links/Related_Topics_Links/Inserting_Related_Topics_Links_into_Topics.htm">Inserting Related Topics Links into Topics</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText></MadCap:conditionalText>. Although a relationship table is a common feature in DITA, you do not need to be using DITA or know anything about DITA in order to take advantage of relationship tables.</p>
